text.tspan: Chaos at PizzaCore: animatronics are dangerous
After six months Rowald Robinson, the
owner of PizzaCore, announced a new
change in his animatronics' software,
all these robotic pets and staff are
being investigated after a group of 3
kids entered the pizzeria without
leaving it. The pizzeria owner claims
the animatronics are not dangerous,
however, the kids are still missing and
the police is doing an intensive search.
The pizzeria is now closed by law and
there is no expected date for its
reopening.
"Our animatronics are 100% safe.
They couldn't do any harm to anyone",
claims Robinson.
PizzaCore is center of attention of everyone since their animatronics are
acting unusual and are a "Possible Danger" according to authorities
The pizzeria is not kid-friendly
anymore: what dark secrets is
it hidding?
